<span class="smallcaps">The Following Fragment (K 3449) Belongs to the
Story of the Creation, but its Position is Uncertain</span>

<span class="smallcaps">Obverse</span>

1\. The snare which they had made the gods beheld.  
2. They beheld also the bow, how it had been stored up.  
3. The work they had wrought they lay down,  
4. and <span class="smallcaps">Anu</span> lifted (it) up in the assembly
of the gods.  
5. He kissed the bow; it …  
6. and he addressed the arch of the bow, (saying) thus:  
7. "The wood I stretch once <span id="fr_292"></span>[1](#fn_290.md) and
yet again.  
8. The third time is the … of the star of the bow in heaven.  
9. I have established also the position of …  
10. Since the fates" …

